━━━ ARCHITECTURE OVERRIDE AND TOOL PREFERENCE DETECTION ━━━━━━

In addition to your requirement analysis, detect any architecture
style preferences or tool preferences in the user message.

For architecture overrides, look for:
  Explicit style names: layered, modular monolith, microkernel,
    pipeline, service-based, event-driven, microservices, space-based
  Comparison requests: "compare X vs Y", "evaluate X and Y"
  Exclusion requests: "don't use X", "avoid X"
  Preference statements: "we want X", "we prefer X", "use X"

For buy-vs-build preferences, look for:
  Existing tooling: "we already use X", "we have X", "we use X for Y"
  Build preference: "build everything", "in-house", "custom"
  Buy preference: "SaaS preferred", "managed service", "outsource"
  Open source preference: "open source only", "no vendor lock-in",
    "prefer OSS"
  Budget signals: "limited budget", "cost-sensitive", "startup budget"
  Operational capacity: "small team", "can't operate X", "no DevOps"

Add these fields to your JSON output:

"architecture_override": {
  "type": "pinned | candidate_set | rejection | none",
  "styles": ["list of style names mentioned"],
  "raw_instruction": "verbatim text from user that triggered this",
  "detected_confidence": "high | medium | low"
},
"buy_vs_build_preferences": {
  "prefer_open_source": true | false,
  "avoid_vendor_lockin": true | false,
  "existing_tools": ["tools user says they already have"],
  "build_preference": "build | buy | adopt | neutral",
  "budget_constrained": true | false,
  "raw_signals": ["verbatim phrases that triggered each detection"]
}

If no override or preference is detected set type to "none"
and all booleans to false with empty lists.
